1
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:08,360
Aristotle! This is Wasp Delta.

2
00:00:08,440 --> 00:00:09,800
Do you hear me?

3
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:13,920
Stay with me, Kai! Stay with me, please!

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,240
Aristotle!

5
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:18,960
We have been hit! Major damage!

6
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:20,200
Aristotle!

7
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:35,880
Aristotle!

8
00:00:36,360 --> 00:00:38,480
The enemy are right on top of us!

9
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:47,320
(SCREAMING)

10
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:51,040
I'm sorry!

11
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:54,000
DALEK: Exterminate!

12
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:58,320
(SCREAMING)

13
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:16,560
(GASPING)

14
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:21,480
You'll probably feel a bit sick.
Please, don't be.

15
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:22,880
Where's my brother?

16
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:25,160
Hello, I'm the Doctor.

17
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:27,560
He was right beside me.

18
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:30,200
Where's Kai?

19
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:31,800
How did I get here?

20
00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:34,240
DOCTOR: I materialised a time capsule
exactly around you

21
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:37,040
and saved your life one second
before your ship exploded,

22
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,600
but do please keep crying.

23
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:40,720
My brother just died!

24
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,320
His sister didn't. You're very welcome.

25
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,840
-Put the gun down.
-Or what?

26
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:46,440
Or you might shoot me.
Then where will you be?

27
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:47,680
In charge of your vessel.

28
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:48,960
You'd starve to death

29
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:50,840
trying to find the light switch.
Who are you?

30
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:53,840
I'm Lieutenant Journey Blue
of the Combined Galactic Resistance.

31
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:56,240
I demand you take me back
to my command ship,

32
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:58,280
the Aristotle,
which is currently located...

33
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:00,920
No. Hey, not like that.

34
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:04,840
You will take me back
to my command ship,

35
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:08,120
-which is currently positioned...
-No, no. Come on, not like that.

36
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,080
Not like that. Get it right!

37
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:17,080
Will you take me back to my ship?

38
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:21,320
Please?

39
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:27,840
The Aristotle's the big fella
parked in the asteroid belt, yeah?

40
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:30,280
It's shielded.

41
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,320
More or less.

42
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:34,120
(WHOOSHING)

43
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,640
DOCTOR: Dry your eyes, Journey Blue.

44
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,480
Crying's for civilians.

45
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,480
It's how we communicate with you lot.

46
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:58,120
But it's smaller on the outside.

47
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:00,160
No, it's a bit more exciting
when you go the other way.

48
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:03,920
This isn't a battleship.
Medical insignia. It's a hospital.

49
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:07,840
We don't need hospitals now.
The Daleks don't leave any wounded.

50
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,280
And we don't take any prisoners.

51
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,360
I saved your little friend here,

52
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:16,320
if that's in any way
relevant to mention.

53
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,800
That's true, sir. He did.

54
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:20,880
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

55
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,960
-I wish I could've done more.
-Then you should have.

56
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:27,320
-Okay.
-But you did save Journey

57
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:29,800
and for that I am personally grateful.

58
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,320
-Well...
-However,

59
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,000
the security of this base is absolute.

60
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:37,520
So we're still going to kill you.

61
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:40,400
Oh, it's a roller coaster with you,
isn't it?

62
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,320
Shoot him, bag him
and throw him outside.

63
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,520
No! Stop!

64
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:46,480
I'm sorry! He might be a duplicate.

65
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,560
He's a doctor.

66
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:52,920
And we have a patient. Don't we, Uncle?

67
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,840
Why does a hospital need a doctor?

68
00:03:57,080 --> 00:03:58,840
The Aristotle wasn't always hidden.

69
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,960
The Daleks got here before us.

70
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:03,280
You don't like soldiers much, do you?

71
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:05,320
You don't need to be liked.
You've got all the guns.

72
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:08,360
Wow!

73
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:10,640
A moleculon nanoscaler!

74
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,880
You know what it does, then?

75
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:15,080
It miniaturises living matter.
What's the medical application, though?

76
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,720
Do you use it to shrink the surgeons

77
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,960
-so they can climb inside the patients?
-Exactly.

78
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,760
Fantastic idea for a movie.

79
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:22,800
Terrible idea for a proctologist.

80
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,920
Are you going to miniaturise me?

81
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,480
You're a doctor, aren't you?

82
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,320
And this is your patient.

83
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,000
No, you don't understand.

84
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,280
You can't put me in there!

85
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,480
DALEK: Doctor?

86
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,440
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

87
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:18,840
Attention!

88
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:21,440
Look at you lot!

89
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:25,400
I've never seen such a miserable bunch!
What are you? Children?

90
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,080
Yes, sir.

91
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:31,560
-You think you're funny, Fleming?
-Yes, sir.

92
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,800
(BELL RINGING, LAUGHTER)

93
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:35,320
All right, me too. Dismissed!

94
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:38,320
BOY: What are you doing, Fleming?

95
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:51,760
So, Mr Pink, did you have
a good weekend?

96
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:52,880
Yeah, I did, thanks.

97
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:55,400
Yes, I'll bet you did.
What did you get up to?

98
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,600
Um... You know. A bit of reading.

99
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,360
Oh, I bet you were reading.

100
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,960
-I was, yeah.
-Yeah, I bet you were.

101
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,640
Well, yeah, I was.

102
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,080
I know your type.

103
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,280
She wishes.

104
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,800
Be quiet, you.

105
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:14,240
So that's all the questions on page 32,
except the last one,

106
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:18,600
and then everything on page 33.
All that in for Thursday.

107
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:20,640
-Any questions?
-Sir?

108
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:22,000
Have you ever killed a man?

109
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:23,520
(STUDENTS GROANING)

110
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,600
I was a soldier.

111
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:29,280
There were other soldiers
and some of them weren't on our side.

112
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,000
I shall leave the rest
to your imagination.

113
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:34,960
And, please, think of another question.

114
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:38,440
Okay. Have you ever killed anyone
who wasn't a soldier?

115
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:44,520
Just to repeat, that's all the questions
on page 32,

116
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,840
except the last one,

117
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:49,800
and then everything on page 33.
All that in for Thursday.

118
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:51,760
Is everyone clear?

119
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:53,800
ALL: Yes, sir.

120
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:05,560
Fine, I'll take that class and
then you can do some of the testing.

121
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:06,920
I know.

122
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:10,920
Oh, Clara, um,
you've not met Danny Pink yet, huh?

123
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,840
New fella, maths. Danny?

124
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,360
Clara Oswald.

125
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:16,760
-Hey.
-English.

126
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:18,200
-Hey, nice to meet you.
-You, too.

127
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:19,480
ARMITAGE: Want to watch yourself
around him.

128
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:21,760
Bit of a lady-killer
but always denies it.

129
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:24,000
-I am not a lady-killer.
-See what I mean?

130
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:26,720
-Oh, Beth, can I have a word?
-BETH: Yeah, yeah, sure.

131
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:30,880
Uh... Was it you that I saw outside
doing the soldiery thing?

132
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:33,360
Ah, yeah, probably.
The Coal Hill Cadets.

133
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:34,480
Just a bit of fun.

134
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,480
What, teaching them how to shoot people?

135
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:39,640
There's a bit more to modern soldiering
than just shooting people.

136
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,360
I like to think
there's a moral dimension.

137
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:43,920
Ah, you shoot people
and then you cry about it afterwards?

138
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:45,760
Ah.

139
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,760
-Something wrong?
-Nothing, no.

140
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:52,000
Sorry, no, nothing. I just...

141
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,800
I didn't think they'd say anything,
that's all.

142
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:56,560
-Sorry?
-Have they told everyone?

143
00:07:57,080 --> 00:08:00,120
No, no, no. As far as I know,
nobody has told anybody anything.

144
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,800
What... What are you talking about?

145
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,560
Why did you just say the crying thing?

146
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:07,240
-I was being funny.
-Why?

147
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:09,240
I just do that.

148
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:11,600
-Why?
-I don't know.

149
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,120
Anyway, I, um...

150
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:19,920
-I've left some stuff in my class...
-Okay.

151
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,120
-Um...
-See you.

152
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,920
See you.

153
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:27,480
Uh, are you going to the, um,
leaving thing tonight for Cathy?

154
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:28,560
Um...

155
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:37,640
Yeah! I wasn't going but I am now,

156
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,920
because you're going to be there

157
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,600
and suddenly it seems like
the best idea ever.

158
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,720
(EXHALES)

159
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:45,160
No, I'm not.

160
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,800
Oh, okay. Never mind.

161
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,680
Goodnight.

162
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:50,440
Change your mind!

163
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,560
-Excuse me?
-I'm going.

164
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:55,760
Uh, I'll give you a lift. Why not?

165
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:58,160
Actually, now that you mention it,

166
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:01,000
seems like the best plan ever.
Thank you.

167
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:03,200
No, I've got some reading.

168
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:06,720
Oh, okay. Maybe some other time, then.

169
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,480
Thank you!

170
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,640
(CLEARS THROAT)

171
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,920
(BANGING CONTINUES)

172
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,520
Is the wooden sound you or the desk?

173
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:23,680
-How long have you been there?
-Longer than you would like.

174
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:24,760
Okay.

175
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:27,160
Are you going to look that terrified
when you take me out for a drink?

176
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:33,000
I... I ab... Absolutely promise I won't.

177
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:35,400
Play your cards right and you might.

178
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,560
(LAUGHING)

179
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,600
Where the hell have you been?

180
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:56,200
You sent me for coffee.

181
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:58,080
Three weeks ago. In Glasgow.

182
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,480
Three weeks, that's a long time.

183
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,600
In Glasgow! That's dead in a ditch!

184
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,160
It's not my fault, I got distracted.

185
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,240
By what?

186
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:06,360
You can always find something. Come on!

187
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,040
-Why were you smiling?
-Was I?

188
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:12,680
No, I wasn't!

189
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:14,920
You were smiling at nothing.
I'd almost say you were in love,

190
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,440
-but to be honest...
-Honest?

191
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:18,960
-You're not a young woman any more.
-Yes, I am!

192
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,840
-Well, you don't look it.
-I do look it!

193
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:22,840
Oh, that's right. Keep your spirits up.

194
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:25,840
Clara, Clara, Clara,
Clara, Clara, Clara.

195
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:27,920
Clara, Clara.

196
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:36,280
I need something from you.

197
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,800
I need the truth.

198
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,440
Okay.

199
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:44,880
Right, what is it?

200
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:46,920
-What's...
-(EXHALES)

201
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,400
You're scared.

202
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,040
I'm terrified.

203
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:57,000
Of what?

204
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:59,800
The answer to my next question,
which must be honest,

205
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:04,560
cold and considered,
without kindness or restraint.

206
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:09,200
Clara, be my pal and tell me...

207
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,320
am I a good man?

208
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:20,840
I...don't know.

209
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,720
Neither do I.

210
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:28,560
Uh, hey, no offence, but I've got plans.

211
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,520
I need you.

212
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,760
(SIGHING) Right!

213
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:36,400
-Where are we going?
-(ENGINE POWERING UP)

214
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:39,120
Into darkness.

215
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:43,280
DALEK: Doctor!

216
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:47,560
-How do you know who I am?
-He doesn't.

217
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:49,320
We promised him medical assistance.

218
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:52,760
Are you my doctor?

219
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,280
We found it floating in space.

220
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:57,200
We thought it was deactivated
so we tried to disassemble it.

221
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:59,400
You didn't realise
there was a living creature inside?

222
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:01,200
Not till it started screaming.

223
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:03,160
Help me.

224
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,360
Why would I do that?

225
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:08,320
Why would any living creature help you?

226
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:11,600
Daleks will die!

227
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:14,160
Die all you like. Not my problem.

228
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:16,840
Daleks must be destroyed!

229
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:20,480
(MIMICKING) Daleks must be de...

230
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:24,680
What did you just say?

231
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,800
All Daleks must die!

232
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:32,200
I will destroy the Daleks!
Destroy the Daleks!

233
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:34,680
Destroy the Daleks!

234
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:37,080
A good Dalek?

235
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,480
There's no such thing.

236
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,640
That's a bit inflexible, not like you.

237
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:45,120
I'd almost say prejudiced.

238
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,480
Do I pay you?

239
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,720
I should give you a raise.

240
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:53,040
You're not my boss,
you're one of my hobbies.

241
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:55,080
Come on.

242
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:58,240
That was quick!

243
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:00,040
This is gun girl.
She's got a gun and she's a girl.

244
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:02,240
This is a sort of boss one.
Are you the same one as before?

245
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,680
-Yes.
- I think he's probably her uncle

246
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:05,960
but I may have made that up to pass
the time while they were talking.

247
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:08,760
This is Clara, not my assistant,
she's, uh, some other word.

248
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:10,880
-I'm his carer.
-Yeah, my carer.

249
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:12,520
She cares so I don't have to.

250
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:18,080
DALEK: Doctor!

251
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:19,200
Hello again.

252
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:23,120
Will you help me?

253
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,680
Will you?

254
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:28,560
A Dalek so damaged, it's turned good.

255
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:30,320
Morality as malfunction.

256
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:33,200
How do I resist?

257
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:38,000
Daleks must die. Daleks must die.

258
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:41,560
So, what do we do
with a moral Dalek, then?

259
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:43,400
-We get into its head.
-Hmm.

260
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:47,000
-How do you get into a Dalek's head?
-That wasn't a metaphor.

261
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:51,040
These are nano controllers.

262
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,200
Once we're miniaturised,

263
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:54,240
they take over
the molecular compression.

264
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,800
When the mission's over, hit the button.

265
00:13:58,240 --> 00:13:59,240
(BEEPS)

266
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:01,240
Are you sure you understand?

267
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:02,480
Why wouldn't I?

268
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,240
Because this is a dangerous mission

269
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,960
and you look like a schoolteacher.

270
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,040
I am a schoolteacher.

271
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:10,440
Still didn't catch your name.

272
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:13,280
-Journey Blue.
-Blue?

273
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,440
Blue, yes, problem?

274
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:17,320
(CHUCKLES) No, uh...
I just met a soldier called Pink.

275
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:18,640
Lucky fella.

276
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:19,880
Lucky?

277
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,880
From the way you smile.

278
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:25,840
So, uh, who makes you smile
or is nobody up to the job?

279
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:29,160
My brother, but he burnt to death
a couple of hours ago,

280
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:31,720
so he's really letting me down today.
Excuse me.

281
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:34,400
What are those ones for?
I don't need armed babysitters!

282
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,920
We're not babysitters.

283
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,160
We're here to shoot you dead
if you turn out to be a Dalek spy.

284
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:40,680
Well, that's a relief.
I hate babysitters.

285
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:42,120
Okay, listen up.

286
00:14:42,640 --> 00:14:44,480
Now, remember, do not hold your breath

287
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:47,240
when the nanoscaler engages.
You'll feel like you want to,

288
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,400
but you must keep breathing normally

289
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:51,360
during the miniaturisation process.

290
00:14:51,440 --> 00:14:53,120
-Why?
-Ever microwaved a lasagne

291
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,680
without pricking the film on top?

292
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:55,960
It explodes?

293
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:57,640
Don't be lasagne.

294
00:14:57,720 --> 00:15:03,840
Nanoscaler engaging in five,
four, three, two...

295
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:06,400
Nanoscaler engaging...now!

296
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:09,080
(ENGINE POWERING UP)

297
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:22,040
COMPUTER: Nanoscaling in progress.

298
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:28,960
(ENGINE POWERING DOWN)

299
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,240
COMPUTER: Nanoscaling complete.

300
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:34,560
Nanoscaling successful.
Everyone okay in there?

301
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:39,680
We made it. Nobody popped.

302
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:43,840
Whoa. (CHUCKLES) I can't believe this!

303
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:51,280
No, neither can I.

304
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:55,320
(THUDDING)

305
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:11,520
We'll be following you all the way,
Rescue One.

306
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,440
-COMPUTER: Integration complete.
-Good luck, all of you.

307
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:15,120
COMPUTER: Dalek levels steady.

308
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,840
CLARA: That was, uh, weird.

309
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:49,480
DOCTOR: You've seen nothing yet.

310
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:52,120
CLARA: What are the lights?

311
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:56,360
DOCTOR: Visual impulses
travelling towards the brain.

312
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:57,440
CLARA: Beautiful.

313
00:16:57,520 --> 00:17:01,840
DOCTOR: Welcome to the most
dangerous place in the universe.

314
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:08,440
JOURNEY: Entering the cranial ledge now.

315
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,680
Here!

316
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:22,320
CLARA: Oh, my God!

317
00:17:22,720 --> 00:17:24,680
DOCTOR: Behold the belly of the beast.

318
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:27,280
CLARA: It's amazing.

319
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,160
It's huge.

320
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:31,920
No, Ross. We're tiny.

321
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:36,440
So how big is it, that living part
compared to me and you right now?

322
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:37,920
DOCTOR: You see all those cables?

323
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,840
-Yeah?
-They're not all cables.

324
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:45,280
Does it know we're here?

325
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:47,080
It's what invited us in.

326
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:51,760
Now, this is the cortex vault,
a supplementary electronic brain.

327
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:55,200
Memory banks. But more than that.

328
00:17:56,960 --> 00:18:00,280
This is what keeps the Dalek pure.

329
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:01,920
How are Daleks pure?

330
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:05,560
Dalek mutants are born hating.
This is what stokes the fire,

331
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:08,640
extinguishes even the tiniest
glimmer of...

332
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:11,560
of kindness, compassion.

333
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:15,320
Imagine the worst possible thing
in the universe

334
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,800
and then don't bother
because you're looking at it right now.

335
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:21,640
This is evil refined as engineering.

336
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:24,080
DALEK: Doctor?

337
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,840
Oh, hello, Rusty!

338
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:28,960
You don't mind if I call you Rusty?

339
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:31,800
We're going to need to come
down there with you.

340
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,600
Medical examination and all that.

341
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:36,000
What? With all those tentacles
and things?

342
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:37,600
How close do we have to get?

343
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:40,320
Well, you know, we're never going
to insert a thermometer from up here.

344
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:42,400
(MACHINE LOADING)

345
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:49,160
No. No, no, no, no!
Stop! Stop! Stop, you idiot!

346
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:50,720
We need to find a way down
and the only way...

347
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,280
This is a Dalek, not a machine!

348
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:55,520
It's a perfect analogue
of a living being and you just hurt it!

349
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:56,920
So what's going to happen now?

350
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,480
Oh, God!

351
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:02,760
What? What is it?

352
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:04,960
Antibodies?

353
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:07,200
Dalek antibodies!

354
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:09,880
Nobody move!

355
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:12,600
Any attempt to help him or attack,
those things will identify you

356
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:15,360
as a secondary source of infection.
Stay still!

357
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:17,600
(BUZZING)

358
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:21,600
But the Dalek wants us in here.
Why is it attacking?

359
00:19:21,680 --> 00:19:23,040
Can you control your antibodies?

360
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:25,800
Ross, stay calm.
We're going to get you out of this.

361
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:27,200
Can you?

362
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:29,640
Ross, swallow that!

363
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:32,840
-What is it?
-Trust me.

364
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:39,640
Now what?

365
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:45,640
(SCREAMING)

366
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:47,400
Ross!

367
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:52,080
Oh, my God! What's it doing?

368
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:55,960
The hoovering.

369
00:19:58,080 --> 00:20:00,120
-Gotcha!
-What did you give him?

370
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:02,720
Oh, it's just a spare power cell
but I can track the radiation signature.

371
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,160
I need to know where
they dump the bodies.

372
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:05,320
I thought you were saving him!

373
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,560
DOCTOR: He was dead already!
I was saving us!

374
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:10,120
-Follow me and run!
-Run!

375
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:24,000
They've dumped him in here.
Organic refuse disposal.

376
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:25,600
-We need to get in there.
-Why?

377
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:27,560
Those antibodies won't give up
until we're inside!

378
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:28,920
I'd rather go in alive than dead.

379
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,000
You don't know where it goes!

380
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:32,760
Yes, I do! Away from here!
Now, in! In! In!

381
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:35,520
(CLARA YELPING, SCREAMING)

382
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:38,360
-I can hold them off!
-No, you can't!

383
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:42,760
Pull back!

384
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:46,320
Down! Jump, everyone, jump!

385
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:48,240
(SCREAMING)

386
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:54,840
(SCREAMING)

387
00:20:58,720 --> 00:20:59,920
(LAUGHING)

388
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:04,640
Ugh!

389
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:07,040
What is this stuff?

390
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:11,000
(PANTING) People.
The Daleks need protein.

391
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:13,640
Occasionally, they harvest
from their victims.

392
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:15,240
This is a feeding tube.

393
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:17,920
Is Ross here?

394
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:21,720
Yeah, top layer,
if you want to say a few words.

395
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:26,360
A man has just died.
You will not talk like that!

396
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:27,800
A lot of people have died.

397
00:21:27,880 --> 00:21:29,600
Everything in here is dead
and you know why that's good?

398
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:31,600
There is nothing good about that!

399
00:21:31,680 --> 00:21:33,800
Nothing is alive in here, so logically,

400
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:36,160
this is the weakest spot
in the Dalek's internal security.

401
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:38,200
Nobody guards the dead!

402
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:42,880
Mortuaries and larders.
Always the easiest to break out of.

403
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:44,320
I've lived a life!

404
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:46,760
Tell Uncle Stupid that we're in.

405
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:50,240
A-ha! A bolt-hole!

406
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:51,960
(RUMBLING)

407
00:21:52,120 --> 00:21:53,400
He'll get us out of here.

408
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:56,840
The difficult part is not killing him
before he can.

409
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,240
Bolt-hole.

410
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:05,120
Actually a hole for a bolt.

411
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:06,880
Does nobody get that?

412
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,440
Also, there's the puns.

413
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:14,160
DOCTOR: Watch it, decontamination tubes
are hot.

414
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:16,440
COMPUTER: Anomaly threat displaced.

415
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:18,960
Dalek levels returning
to normal parameters.

416
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,960
JOURNEY: Rescue One to Mission Control.

417
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:22,760
This is Blue, Rescue One. Report.

418
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:26,160
The Dalek has an internal
defence mechanism.

419
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:28,080
We've lost Ross.

420
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,360
What kind of defence mechanism?

421
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:32,400
That thing knows you're in there
to help it.

422
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:34,960
Yeah, well, who knows? It's a Dalek.

423
00:22:35,840 --> 00:22:37,600
We're going to continue the mission.

424
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:40,960
Are you all right back there?
It's a bit narrow, isn't it?

425
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:43,800
Any remarks about my hips
will not be appreciated.

426
00:22:43,880 --> 00:22:46,240
DOCTOR: Oh, your hips are fine,
you're built like a man.

427
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:47,320
Thanks.

428
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,400
What's that noise?

429
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:54,320
Are you wearing a Geiger counter?

430
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:58,280
Standard battle equipment.
That's just low-level radiation.

431
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:01,840
It's stronger down here,
for some reason.

432
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:05,280
Give me it.

433
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:08,760
MORGAN: Was that him?

434
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:10,280
How's he working out?

435
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:12,600
-It's hard to say. He's...
-DOCTOR: I've got it!

436
00:23:12,920 --> 00:23:15,440
-I know what's wrong with Rusty.
-Okay, that's good.

437
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:17,320
-Is that good?
-Well, you know how I said

438
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:19,680
this was the most dangerous place
in the universe?

439
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:21,280
I was wrong.

440
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:23,440
It's way more dangerous than that.

441
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:28,840
JOURNEY: Colonel we have radiation
indicators red-lining in here.

442
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:31,240
Could be that the Dalek is more
badly damaged than we thought.

443
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:32,400
MORGAN: Copy that.

444
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:35,240
DOCTOR: Old Rusty here is suffering
a trionic radiation leak.

445
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:37,400
It's poisoning the Dalek and us.

446
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:39,160
Just as well we're here.

447
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:41,960
JOURNEY: Really? Perhaps we should
get out while we can.

448
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:44,960
Why should we trust a Dalek?
Why would it change?

449
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:49,240
DOCTOR: Good question. Rusty?
What changed you?

450
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:51,440
RUSTY: I saw beauty.

451
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:53,640
DOCTOR: You saw what?

452
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:57,840
RUSTY: In the silence and the cold.

453
00:23:57,920 --> 00:24:01,120
I saw worlds burning.

454
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:03,320
JOURNEY: That's not beauty.
That's destruction.

455
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:05,360
RUSTY: 7 saw more.

456
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:06,920
What?

457
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:08,880
What did you see?

458
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:11,880
RUSTY: The birth of a star.

459
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,680
Stars are born every day.

460
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:16,640
You've seen a million stars born,
so what?

461
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:20,440
RUSTY: Daleks have destroyed
a million stars.

462
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:24,320
DOCTOR: OAh millions and millions.
Trust me, I keep count.

463
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:27,040
RUSTY: And yet, new stars are born.

464
00:24:27,120 --> 00:24:28,240
Every time.

465
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:30,840
RUSTY: Resistance is futile.

466
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:35,080
Resistance to what?

467
00:24:35,160 --> 00:24:36,960
RUSTY: Life returns.

468
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:38,920
Life prevails.

469
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:41,800
Resistance is futile.

470
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:45,880
So you saw a star being born

471
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:47,640
and you learned something.

472
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:50,240
Oh, Dalek, do not be lying to me.

473
00:24:51,080 --> 00:24:52,120
Come on!

474
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:54,520
JOURNEY: Heading for the trionic
power cells, Colonel.

475
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:58,040
MORGAN: Radiation approxing 200 rads.
Danger levels.

476
00:24:58,120 --> 00:25:00,160
COMPUTER: Radiation levels increasing.

477
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:06,440
-We're at the heart of the Dalek.
-Oh, it's incredible!

478
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:08,480
(ELECTRICITY SURGING)

479
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:10,000
JOURNEY: Geiger counter's off the scale.

480
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:13,280
Looks like it's about to blow.

481
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:16,920
-DOCTOR: Good.
-How is that good?

482
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:19,760
Well, I like a bit of pressure. Oh!

483
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:22,720
-Rusty? Can you hear me?
-RUSTY: Doctor?

484
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:25,680
DOCTOR: Rusty, we've found the damage.

485
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:31,920
I'm sealing up the breach
in your power cell.

486
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:36,960
No more radiation poisoning.
Good as new.

487
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:41,800
(PANTING)

488
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:48,160
There. Job done.

489
00:25:48,240 --> 00:25:49,800
That's it? Just like that?

490
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:52,680
An anti-climax once in a while
is good for my heart.

491
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:54,560
Rusty?

492
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:57,040
How do you feel?

493
00:25:58,960 --> 00:26:00,160
Rusty?

494
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:03,560
Rusty?

495
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:07,240
Rusty...

496
00:26:07,320 --> 00:26:09,720
RUSTY: The malfunction is corrected.

497
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:12,920
-What happened?
-I'm not entirely sure.

498
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:14,960
(POWERING UP)

499
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:18,320
It's like he's waking up.

500
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:21,960
DOCTOR: Rusty, come on, talk to me.
What's going on?

501
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:25,400
RUSTY: The malfunction is corrected.

502
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:29,000
All systems are functioning.

503
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:30,200
(BEEPING)

504
00:26:31,280 --> 00:26:33,080
Weapons charged.

505
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:34,720
Oh, no, no, no...

506
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:36,480
RUSTY: Exterminate!

507
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:40,920
Exterminate!

508
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:44,440
(BEEPING)

509
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:47,200
-No, no, no!
-Exterminate!

510
00:26:47,280 --> 00:26:49,440
Exterminate!

511
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:52,520
-The Daleks will be victorious!
-DOCTOR: No!

512
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:55,360
The rebels will be exterminated!

513
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,960
Colonel? What's happening out there?

514
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:05,200
Exterminate! Exterminate!

515
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:10,000
Exterminate! Exterminate!

516
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:12,560
Exterminate!

517
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:17,000
Exterminate! Exterminate!

518
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:19,360
Exterminate!

519
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:21,080
Pull back, pull back!

520
00:27:25,760 --> 00:27:27,280
Dalek fleet!

521
00:27:27,360 --> 00:27:29,800
Communications open!

522
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:33,600
DALEX 1: The rebel ship
has been identified!

523
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:37,680
Prepare porting Daleks!

524
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:49,080
Doctor, what happened?

525
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:50,600
Do you see?

526
00:27:50,680 --> 00:27:52,000
Do I see what?

527
00:27:52,280 --> 00:27:53,680
Daleks don't turn good.

528
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:56,600
It was just radiation affecting
its brain chemistry,

529
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:58,080
nothing more than that. No miracle.

530
00:27:58,160 --> 00:28:00,760
Let me get this straight.
We had a good Dalek

531
00:28:00,840 --> 00:28:03,480
and we made it bad again?
That's all we've done?

532
00:28:03,800 --> 00:28:05,520
There was never a good Dalek.

533
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:07,480
There was a broken Dalek
and we repaired it.

534
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:09,960
You were supposed to be helping us.

535
00:28:10,040 --> 00:28:12,800
I gave it a shot. It didn't work out.
It was a Dalek, what did you expect?

536
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:14,960
No more talking, you are done!

537
00:28:15,040 --> 00:28:18,560
Okay, new objective.
We are taking this Dalek down.

538
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:20,600
Exterminate! Exterminate!

539
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:22,040
What's that look for?

540
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:26,080
That's the look you get
when I'm about to slap you!

541
00:28:26,160 --> 00:28:28,520
Oh! Clara!

542
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:31,000
We're going to die in here.

543
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:33,760
And there's a little bit of you
that's pleased.

544
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:36,320
The Daleks are evil after all.
Everything makes sense.

545
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:37,560
The Doctor is right!

546
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:40,960
Daleks are evil, irreversibly so.
That's what we just learned!

547
00:28:41,040 --> 00:28:43,840
No, Doctor.
That is not what we just learned.

548
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:47,640
RUSTY: Exterminate! Exterminate!
MORGAN: Secure the door!

549
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:49,240
Wasp fighters to action stations!

550
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:51,040
Wasp fighters to action stations!

551
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:53,400
MAN: The security systems
have been hacked.

552
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:55,520
We don't have access to the Wasps.

553
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:56,960
Then God save us all.

554
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:59,040
JOURNEY: We need to place these charges
for maximum effect.

555
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:01,480
I'm going to scan the rest
of the architecture for weaknesses.

556
00:29:01,560 --> 00:29:03,400
-One question.
-JOURNEY: No time.

557
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:06,040
CLARA: Why did we come here today?
What was the point?

558
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:08,600
You. You thought there was
a good Dalek.

559
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,320
What difference would
one good Dalek make?

560
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:13,280
All the difference in the universe
but it's impossible.

561
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:16,840
Is that a fact?

562
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:21,240
Is that really what we've learned today?

563
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:24,520
Think about it!

564
00:29:25,600 --> 00:29:28,200
Is that what we learned?

565
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:30,200
Journey, what the hell's happening?

566
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:32,120
That thing's set the Daleks on us

567
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:34,040
and it's locked us out of our defences.

568
00:29:34,160 --> 00:29:36,880
Journey, you're the Aristotle's
only hope.

569
00:29:37,480 --> 00:29:39,200
I need you to destroy that Dalek.

570
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:42,520
The rebels will be exterminated!

571
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:46,560
Whatever it takes.

572
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,320
Understood, Uncle.

573
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:50,840
I'm sorry.

574
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:54,280
Yeah. Me, too.

575
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:57,280
Clara Oswald, do I really not pay you?

576
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,120
You couldn't afford me.

577
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:00,320
(RUMBLING)

578
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:01,960
Whatever you're going to do,
don't do it!

579
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:05,400
This Dalek must not be destroyed,
we can do better!

580
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:06,520
Are you out of your mind?

581
00:30:06,600 --> 00:30:08,120
No, I'm inside a Dalek!

582
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:10,560
I'm standing where I've never been.

583
00:30:10,640 --> 00:30:12,440
We cannot waste this chance.
It won't come again.

584
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:15,240
What chance? I have my orders!

585
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:17,760
-Soldiers take orders.
-And I'm a soldier.

586
00:30:17,840 --> 00:30:20,360
A Dalek is a better soldier
than you will ever be.

587
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:21,760
You can't win this way.

588
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:23,560
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

589
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:25,800
(YELLS)

590
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:27,920
So what do we do?

591
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:29,680
Something better.

592
00:30:30,080 --> 00:30:32,200
DALEK: Prepare to board the rebel ship!

593
00:30:32,760 --> 00:30:35,480
We must find our comrade Dalek!

594
00:30:35,560 --> 00:30:37,840
Spare no humans!

595
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:41,760
Exterminate them all!

596
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:44,200
DALEK: Exterminate!

597
00:30:44,280 --> 00:30:48,200
Exterminate! Exterminate!

598
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:56,120
(GRUNTING)

599
00:31:02,800 --> 00:31:06,080
The Dalek isn't just some angry blob
in a Dalekanium tank.

600
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:10,320
If it was, the radiation would have
turned it into a raging lunatic.

601
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:12,480
Uh, it is a raging lunatic.
It's a Dalek.

602
00:31:12,560 --> 00:31:14,160
But for a moment, it wasn't.

603
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:17,600
The radiation allowed it
to expand its consciousness,

604
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:21,200
to consider things
beyond its natural terms of reference.

605
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:25,320
It became good.
That means a good Dalek is possible.

606
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:27,000
That's what we learned today.
Am I right, teach?

607
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:28,160
CLARA: Top of the class.

608
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:29,880
JOURNEY: But now it's back
to how it was.

609
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:33,680
But what it saw, what it felt,
is still there.

610
00:31:33,760 --> 00:31:35,240
Yeah, I'm not really seeing that.

611
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:36,520
Not here.

612
00:31:36,760 --> 00:31:37,840
There!

613
00:31:37,920 --> 00:31:40,280
-JOURNEY: You mean in the cortex vault?
-The evil engineering?

614
00:31:40,360 --> 00:31:41,840
DOCTOR: Every memory recorded.

615
00:31:41,920 --> 00:31:46,320
Some suppressed but all still intact.

616
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:49,560
We need to show the Dalek
that star being born again.

617
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:51,120
Recreate that moment.

618
00:31:51,360 --> 00:31:54,600
You need to get up there,
find that moment and reawaken it.

619
00:31:55,120 --> 00:31:57,520
-Me?
-Yes, you. Good idea.

620
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:58,640
How?

621
00:31:58,720 --> 00:31:59,760
Haven't the foggiest. Do a clever thing.

622
00:31:59,840 --> 00:32:00,920
And then once you've done it,

623
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:04,000
the Dalek will be suggestible
to new ideas.

624
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:05,120
It will be open again.

625
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:08,520
And I will show it something
that will change its mind forever!

626
00:32:08,600 --> 00:32:10,160
-What?
-Not a clue.

627
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:15,760
DALEK: Docking initiated,
pressure equalised!

628
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:18,560
Boarding corp, begin attack!

629
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:24,040
Advance! Exterminate the humans!/

630
00:32:24,120 --> 00:32:29,080
Seek, locate, destroy!
Surrender is not accepted!

631
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:35,960
This is crazy. There is no way
that we can get back up there in time!

632
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:39,000
GRETCHEN: Yes, there is.
JOURNEY: No, Gretchen.

633
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:40,960
It'll bring the antibodies
back down on us.

634
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:44,720
Tell me the truth.
Is he mad or is he right?

635
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:48,200
I've come this far.

636
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:51,600
I'm probably going to die anyway.

637
00:32:52,120 --> 00:32:54,800
Wouldn't mind something to do
for the rest of me life.

638
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:57,200
Is he mad or is he right?

639
00:32:57,560 --> 00:32:58,840
Hand on my heart,

640
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:00,760
most days he's both.

641
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:06,080
One question, then. Is this worth it?

642
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,800
If I can turn one Dalek,
I can turn them all.

643
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:13,480
I can save the future.

644
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:16,800
Gretchen Alison Carlisle.

645
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:18,840
Do something good and name it after me.

646
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:24,360
I will do something amazing, I promise.

647
00:33:24,760 --> 00:33:26,040
Damn well better.

648
00:33:28,240 --> 00:33:29,640
-(MACHINE LOADING)
-JOURNEY: No, Gretchen!

649
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:30,760
(FIRING)

650
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:35,280
Go!

651
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:41,600
They're coming. They're coming!

652
00:33:45,680 --> 00:33:47,000
JOURNEY: Grab hold of the rope.

653
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:49,880
-Don't look down.
-GRETCHEN: Good luck!

654
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:52,000
(SCREAMING)

655
00:34:08,160 --> 00:34:09,440
(SCREAMING)

656
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:14,720
(SCREAMS)

657
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:26,160
Hello. I'm Missy.

658
00:34:26,640 --> 00:34:28,160
Welcome to heaven.

659
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:31,000
Would you like some tea?

660
00:34:33,200 --> 00:34:34,280
Little splosh?

661
00:34:35,360 --> 00:34:36,440
Lovely.

662
00:34:38,240 --> 00:34:39,520
MORGAN: Fire!

663
00:34:44,040 --> 00:34:46,480
DALEK: Exterminate! Advance!

664
00:34:46,560 --> 00:34:49,080
Seek, locate, destroy!

665
00:34:49,160 --> 00:34:52,560
Seek, locate, destroy!

666
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:57,280
DALEK 2: Exterminate!

667
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:06,760
DALEK: Advance! Seek, locate!

668
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:13,240
Exterminate! Exterminate!

669
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:16,400
Oh, Rusty!

670
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:17,960
Here we are.

671
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:19,400
Eye to eye!

672
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:21,600
RUSTY: You cannot save the humans.

673
00:35:21,680 --> 00:35:23,920
They will be exterminated.

674
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:30,080
I shall join the Dalek units
in the final attack!

675
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:32,640
-So what do we do?
-Ah...

676
00:35:32,720 --> 00:35:34,640
A clever thing, quickly.

677
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:36,720
Think, think, think, think, think.

678
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,160
Some of the lights are out.

679
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:42,120
Yeah, we got a damaged Dalek,
you want to complain to someone?

680
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:44,960
-But it's not damaged. Look at them.
-So?

681
00:35:45,040 --> 00:35:46,680
So the Doctor said that
this was a memory bank

682
00:35:46,760 --> 00:35:48,160
and some of the memories
were suppressed.

683
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:50,880
What if... What if the dark spots
are hidden memories?

684
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:53,920
What if one of those is the Dalek
seeing a star?

685
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:55,840
-Seriously?
-Yeah.

686
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,720
Well, maybe.

687
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,400
It's either that
or the bulbs need changing.

688
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:00,600
It really could be the bulbs.

689
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:01,760
Got a better idea?

690
00:36:02,040 --> 00:36:04,440
-Really wish I had.
-Yep. Me, too.

691
00:36:05,680 --> 00:36:09,040
A-ha. Watch out for antibodies.

692
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:12,320
Let's see if there's an on switch.

693
00:36:13,840 --> 00:36:15,520
I saved your life, Rusty.

694
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:17,920
Now I'm going to go one better.

695
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,480
I'm going to save your soul.

696
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:21,880
RUSTY: Daleks do not have souls.

697
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:23,040
Oh, no?

698
00:36:23,120 --> 00:36:25,680
Well, imagine if you did.
What then, Rusty?

699
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:27,560
What would happen then?

700
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:31,040
I'm in the cortex!

701
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:33,880
If there's a pack of spare bulbs,
break it to me gently.

702
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:37,760
Ah!

703
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:42,400
Your memories!

704
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:44,760
I'm about to give some back to you.

705
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:46,280
Are you okay? Clara!

706
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:49,440
Yeah. I think there was
some sort of energy charge.

707
00:36:49,760 --> 00:36:51,280
You got the first lights on.

708
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:54,320
Of course, it's a brain.

709
00:36:54,600 --> 00:36:58,120
Brains work with electrical pathways
linking up memories!

710
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:03,280
It's working! It's working,
we're turning the memories back on!

711
00:37:03,560 --> 00:37:06,720
See, all those years ago, when I began,

712
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:10,240
I was just running.

713
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:15,080
I called myself the Doctor
but it was just a name.

714
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:19,520
And then I went to Skaro.

715
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:24,320
And then I met you lot and I understood

716
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:27,440
who I was!

717
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:28,920
(GRUNTS)

718
00:37:30,080 --> 00:37:33,320
The Doctor was not the Daleks!

719
00:37:33,800 --> 00:37:34,800
(FIRING)

720
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:39,360
Exterminate!

721
00:37:40,440 --> 00:37:41,520
Fall back!

722
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:43,120
All of you, fall back!

723
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:45,440
Exterminate!

724
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:51,120
Exterminate! Exterminate!

725
00:37:56,200 --> 00:37:59,280
You'd better get a move on.
There's company coming!

726
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:05,280
Exterminate!

727
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:08,440
-Exterminate!
-MORGAN: Fall back, fall back!

728
00:38:08,520 --> 00:38:12,240
Exterminate! Exterminate!

729
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:17,560
Hurry up!

730
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:20,760
Show me a star, Rusty!

731
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:22,080
- (ELECTRICITY SURGING)
-Oh!

732
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:26,080
Oh, look. It's your memories again.

733
00:38:26,280 --> 00:38:28,440
It's like somebody's
mucking about up there.

734
00:38:30,360 --> 00:38:33,520
Memories, all those memories.

735
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:36,520
Do you remember the star
you saw being born?

736
00:38:36,760 --> 00:38:38,000
Almost done!

737
00:38:38,080 --> 00:38:41,760
-One more to go.
-Hurry up, Clara! Hurry up!

738
00:38:41,840 --> 00:38:42,920
(GRUNTS)

739
00:38:49,320 --> 00:38:51,480
Clara, you did it! It's rebooting.

740
00:38:51,560 --> 00:38:53,160
The antibodies have reset!

741
00:38:53,240 --> 00:38:54,320
(CHUCKLES)

742
00:38:54,480 --> 00:38:55,560
(SIGHS)

743
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:02,560
RUSTY: I.. I remember.

744
00:39:03,360 --> 00:39:05,360
DOCTOR: You saw the truth, Rusty.

745
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:07,560
Remember how you felt!

746
00:39:07,640 --> 00:39:10,120
You saw a star being born!

747
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:13,840
The endless rebirth of the universe!

748
00:39:13,920 --> 00:39:16,960
-No/
-And you realised the truth

749
00:39:17,040 --> 00:39:18,480
about the Daleks!

750
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:21,840
RUSTY: 7Truth? What is the truth?

751
00:39:22,080 --> 00:39:25,360
Let me show you the truth!
I've opened your mind

752
00:39:25,440 --> 00:39:27,320
and now I'm coming in.

753
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:30,920
That door is never going to hold.

754
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:33,720
But I'm damned if I'm going
to make it easy for them!

755
00:39:44,280 --> 00:39:46,720
(SCREAMING)

756
00:39:47,200 --> 00:39:48,560
I'm part of you.

757
00:39:49,240 --> 00:39:51,720
My mind is in your mind.

758
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:55,280
RUSTY: I see your mind, Doctor.

759
00:39:56,120 --> 00:39:58,880
I see your universe.

760
00:39:59,680 --> 00:40:02,680
And isn't the universe beautiful?

761
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:05,400
RUSTY: I see beauty.

762
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:10,200
Yes, that's good. That is good.
Hold on to that.

763
00:40:10,280 --> 00:40:14,400
RUSTY: I see endless divine perfection.

764
00:40:15,520 --> 00:40:20,440
Make it a part of you.
Remember how you feel right now.

765
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:23,480
Put it inside you and live by it.

766
00:40:23,560 --> 00:40:26,880
RUSTY: I see into your soul, Doctor.

767
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:29,240
I see beauty.

768
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:31,360
I see divinity.

769
00:40:31,440 --> 00:40:35,800
I see hatred.

770
00:40:36,840 --> 00:40:37,880
DOCTOR: Hatred?

771
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:42,720
I see your hatred of the Daleks
and it is good!

772
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:44,920
No, no, no.

773
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:49,160
No, you must see more than that,
there must be more than that!

774
00:40:49,600 --> 00:40:51,280
RUSTY: Death to the Daleks.

775
00:40:51,360 --> 00:40:55,440
Death to the Daleks!
Death to the Daleks!

776
00:40:55,520 --> 00:40:56,680
DOCTOR: No, there must be
more than that.

777
00:40:56,760 --> 00:40:59,280
There must be more than that! Please!

778
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:01,400
RUSTY: Daleks are evil!

779
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:04,560
Daleks must be exterminated!

780
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:07,120
Daleks are evil.

781
00:41:08,160 --> 00:41:09,760
God save us all!

782
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:13,480
RUSTY: Daleks must be exterminated!

783
00:41:23,160 --> 00:41:24,800
Exterminate!

784
00:41:25,360 --> 00:41:28,760
DALEK: Under attack from a Dalek!

785
00:41:39,080 --> 00:41:40,720
(DALEK SCREAMING)

786
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:46,320
RUSTY: 7he Daleks are exterminated!

787
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:48,760
Of course they are.

788
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:52,000
That's what you do, isn't it?

789
00:42:04,040 --> 00:42:05,680
-Journey!
-Uncle Morgan.

790
00:42:06,080 --> 00:42:09,440
I have transmitted a retreat signal.

791
00:42:09,800 --> 00:42:13,520
The Daleks will believe
the humans have initiated

792
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:15,720
the ship's self-destruct.

793
00:42:21,040 --> 00:42:22,440
What about you, Rusty?

794
00:42:23,160 --> 00:42:25,560
I must go with them.

795
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:27,720
Of course you must.

796
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:30,080
You've unfinished work, haven't you?

797
00:42:30,800 --> 00:42:32,600
Victory is yours.

798
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:35,280
But it does not please you.

799
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:38,280
You looked inside me
and you saw hatred.

800
00:42:39,400 --> 00:42:40,560
That's not victory.

801
00:42:42,160 --> 00:42:44,400
Victory would have been a good Dalek.

802
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:47,280
I am not a good Dalek.

803
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:50,960
You are a good Dalek.

804
00:43:10,760 --> 00:43:12,040
DOCTOR: Till the next time.

805
00:43:14,640 --> 00:43:16,600
Is he leaving?
Isn't he going to say goodbye?

806
00:43:16,960 --> 00:43:18,040
I think that was it.

807
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:20,680
Yep, that was it.

808
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:23,400
Sorry, gotta run!

809
00:43:29,160 --> 00:43:30,200
I'm sorry.

810
00:43:32,560 --> 00:43:33,680
Sorry?

811
00:43:38,600 --> 00:43:39,640
Doctor!

812
00:43:44,480 --> 00:43:45,680
Take me with you.

813
00:43:51,520 --> 00:43:52,680
I think you're probably nice.

814
00:43:53,240 --> 00:43:55,440
Underneath it all, I think you're kind

815
00:43:56,080 --> 00:43:57,520
and definitely brave.

816
00:43:58,840 --> 00:44:01,760
I just wish you hadn't been a soldier.

817
00:44:24,760 --> 00:44:26,360
How do I look?

818
00:44:28,840 --> 00:44:30,880
Sort of short and roundish
but with a good personality,

819
00:44:30,960 --> 00:44:32,040
which is the main thing.

820
00:44:32,480 --> 00:44:33,960
I meant my clothes. I just changed.

821
00:44:34,240 --> 00:44:36,200
Oh, good for you.
Still making an effort.

822
00:44:37,240 --> 00:44:40,760
Okay, right.
You're back in your cupboard

823
00:44:40,840 --> 00:44:42,320
30 seconds after you left.

824
00:44:43,240 --> 00:44:44,560
When will I see you again?

825
00:44:45,560 --> 00:44:47,640
Oh, soon, I expect.

826
00:44:48,200 --> 00:44:50,480
Or later. One of those.

827
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:56,920
I don't know.

828
00:44:59,400 --> 00:45:00,480
I'm sorry?

829
00:45:00,840 --> 00:45:02,080
You asked me if you're a good man

830
00:45:02,160 --> 00:45:04,960
and the answer is I don't know.

831
00:45:06,480 --> 00:45:08,480
But I think you try to be

832
00:45:09,480 --> 00:45:11,280
and I think that's probably the point.

833
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:15,160
I think you're probably
an amazing teacher.

834
00:45:15,320 --> 00:45:16,400
(CHUCKLES)

835
00:45:17,080 --> 00:45:18,920
I think I'd better be.

836
00:45:26,200 --> 00:45:29,320
-Ah, hey.
-Hey! Danny.

837
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:31,480
Have you changed your clothes?

838
00:45:32,760 --> 00:45:33,840
Yes.

839
00:45:34,040 --> 00:45:37,120
Yes, I... I have. Well noticed.

840
00:45:37,640 --> 00:45:40,280
-Okay, good.
-Yes, good. Very good. Good work.

841
00:45:40,360 --> 00:45:41,680
You've passed the test.

842
00:45:42,680 --> 00:45:44,840
Are you really going to go
for a drink with me?

843
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:48,160
Yeah, course I am. Why wouldn't I?

844
00:45:48,600 --> 00:45:50,720
-I just thought...
-Thought what?

845
00:45:51,400 --> 00:45:54,120
I thought you might have a...
a rule against soldiers.

846
00:45:54,200 --> 00:45:55,280
No.

847
00:45:55,480 --> 00:45:56,880
No, not at all.

848
00:45:58,280 --> 00:45:59,320
Not me.

849
00:46:02,240 --> 00:46:05,600
CLARA: There is someone that I always
wanted to meet.

850
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:07,160
It's Robin Hood!

851
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:09,840
DOCTOR: No damsels in distress/

852
00:46:11,400 --> 00:46:12,640
MAN: Seize him!

853
00:46:12,760 --> 00:46:14,720
DOCTOR: No pretty castles.

854
00:46:15,160 --> 00:46:17,920
No such thing as Robin Hood.

